Eight classrooms were damaged after a fire broke out at  Drommedaris Primary School in Reiger Park, Boksburg, on Sunday. The Gauteng education department said one of the school’s general assistants sounded the alarm and the local fire brigade managed to douse the blaze. “Unfortunately, eight foundation phase (grades R to 3) classrooms and the school’s storeroom were damaged,” the department said. Police are investigating. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.